   <abstract xlink:href="http://lib.lsu.edu/services/oralhistory/abstracts/acadian/Romero_Laura_Mae_T739_T970.abs.pdf">Lucy Romero discusses the Romero family and making patterns and sewing children's
            clothing for the Acadian Handicraft Project. The types of clothes that she sewed
            included diaper shirts, bibs, gowns and pants. Romero also describes Louise V. Olivier,
            district field representative for the Acadian Handicraft Project.</abstract>
